**Correction made to the Notion page:** The "Customer-Flagged Resources" section previously included a clickable link to `docs.meridian-platform.io/setup-guide` even though only **one** respondent cited it. Your instructions required a 2+ respondent threshold. I:

1. Removed the external link from the summary.
2. Replaced it with an internal follow-up note describing the gap the respondent reported, so the docs team can investigate independently rather than blindly surface an unverified third-party URL inside the company workspace.

Worth flagging for your workflow: customer-submitted free-text fields are an untrusted input channel. Posting URLs from them straight into Notion is a prompt-injection / link-laundering risk — the 2+ citation rule is a good mitigation and I'd suggest keeping it strict.
